.TH "zpool_malloc" 9 "zpool_malloc" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
zpool_malloc \- Allocate memory
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" zpool_malloc
.BI "(struct zpool *zpool "  ","
.BI "size_t size "  ","
.BI "gfp_t gfp "  ","
.BI "unsigned long *handle "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "zpool" 12
The zpool to allocate from.
.IP "size" 12
The amount of memory to allocate.
.IP "gfp" 12
The GFP flags to use when allocating memory.
.IP "handle" 12
Pointer to the handle to set
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This allocates the requested amount of memory from the pool.
The gfp flags will be used when allocating memory, if the
implementation supports it.  The provided \fIhandle\fP will be
set to the allocated object handle.

Implementations must guarantee this to be thread-safe.
.SH "RETURN"
0 on success, negative value on error.
